id: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training-PH: + Washington, DC United States-Event Brite
name: Organizational Skills 1 Day Training
description:
Through Organizational Skills you will encounter improved productivity, better management, and an overall increase in professional growth.
Everyday people waste numerous amounts of time looking for items.
So stop looking for those important items, and start knowing where they are by getting organized.
Target Audience: Anybody who is interested in learning Organizational Skills.
Learning Objectives:● By the end of this course you will be able to: Remove the Clutter Prioritize Scheduling Your Time To Do Lists Paper and Paperless Storage Organization Your Work Area Tools to Fight Procrastination Organizing your Inbox Avoid the Causes of Disorganization Discipline is the Key to Stay Organized Prerequisites: None Course Materials: Attendees will receive a course manual with presentation slides and reference materials.

id: Free First Home Buyers Evening | 14th August 2025 | Motueka- Wallace Street Motueka, Tasman Region-Event Brite
name: Free First Home Buyers Evening | 14th August 2025 | Motueka
description:
Are you thinking about buying your first home?
Join Alice Ridgen, Mortgage Mentor from NZHL Nelson Bays, for an informative evening focused on helping first home buyers navigate the property market with confidence.
Alice will share her expert insights into the current local market and highlight how receiving the right advice at the right time can make a meaningful difference in your home-buying journey.
The seminar will cover essential financial considerations, including budgeting, deposit planning, and understanding your borrowing capacity, to help you best prepare effectively for your first home purchase.
Whether you're just starting to think about buying or you're ready to take the next step, this is a valuable opportunity to gain practical knowledge, ask questions, and receive guidance from an experienced mortgage expert.

id: Action Overlands Guest Speaker Series: Marin Hobson Optics Specialist- Wareham Place Lower Hutt, Wellington Region-Event Brite
name: Action Overlands Guest Speaker Series: Marin Hobson Optics Specialist
venue: Wareham Place Lower Hutt, Wellington Region
description:
Welcome to the Action Overlands Guest Speaker Series: Marin Hobson level up your hunt !
See the night like never before.
🔦 Join us for an exclusive evening with Marin Hobson, the outdoorsman and digital optics specialist behind Kiwidad Adventures (95k+ followers!).
This FREE, hands-on event is perfect for hunters, and adventurers who want to step up their game.
What to expect: A deep dive into Hikmicro’s cutting-edge thermal and night vision range – scopes, monoculars, and clip-ons Pro tips & tricks for getting the best performance in the field Hands-on time with the gear A relaxed mix and mingle session with nibbles and drinks Spots are limited – secure your free ticket today!

id: Awa-side | Grassroots Up- Laings Road Lower Hutt, Wellington-Event Brite
name: Awa-side | Grassroots Up
description:
What's on your palette?
Through guided prompts and making, we’ll respond to our current realities and future hopes, using art to uncover what we need more (or less) of.
No right way to do it.
Bring a friend and show up, create, and connect.
All materials, kai and drinks provided.

id: LOSST Round 6- Vivian Street Wellington, Wellington-Event Brite
name: LOSST Round 6
description:
Returning to our favourite stomping ground this August, Jedi, Ludus, Lazy Daisy, Mr Meaty Boy and Pothos are set to cause a stir.
We know Pōneke likes to treat us to a marvellous Winter, but why not create a storm of our own... Techno and breaks are presumed to be expected, but one never truly knows which way the wind will blow.

name: Wellington Audio Tour: A Journey Through Culture, Governance, and Nature
venue: Bank of New Zealand Te Aro branch building Victoria Street, Wellington Central, Wellington, New ZealandVictoria St Wellington,
description:
Embark on the Wellington Wonders: A Journey Through Culture, Governance, and Nature – Your Personal Adventure in Wellington!
Wander through historic streets, uncover hidden gems, and let the city's rich tapestry of stories unfold at your own pace.
🗺️ Tour Details Duration: 1 hour 20 minutes Distance: Around 3.6 km (2.2 miles) Audio Content: up to 28min Stops: 11 captivating landmarks including Archives New Zealand, Radio New Zealand, Reserve Bank of New Zealand Experience the charm of Wellington like never before.
Enter the code, and you're all set to explore Wellington on your terms.
It doesn't matter which date or time you select, when you redeem the code, the audio tour will be available to you permanently so you can explore on any day.
